author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
KFC’s buckets were born in 1957, when a franchisee filled a cheap but sturdy container with chicken, rolls and gravy—a full meal that helped make KFC one of America’s biggest fast-food chains. It has also become one of KFC’s biggest obstacles.

#KFC #Food #WSJ
title: KFC Lost Fast Food's Chicken Crown. Here's How It Plans to Win It Back
